title: Grateful Dead Live at Los Angeles Coliseum on 1991-06-01
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street, Walkin' Blues, Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Candyman, Queen Jane Approximately, Deal

Set 2

Picasso Moon, Foolish Heart, Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Black Peter-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Keep Shaking Surprised no one has reviewed this show.  Had an audience tape right after show and always liked the Shakedown, Greatest Story, Bertha opener.  Some good interaction with Garcia and Hornsby.  Bob's guitar sounds great in the mix. Big bass sound on the soundboard.  Average show for '91 but an off tour adventure in LA.

Also Surprised... ...that no one had reviewed except for one poster minutes before me.  I saw low ratings and read bad reviews on other recordings, but halfway through set 2 and it sounds pretty good to me - no doubt aided by Mr. Miller.  Solid 3.5, rounding up to 4 to give it some love!
